.TH "CSSSTYLERULE.STYLE" "3JS" "November 25, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
CSSStyleRule.style \- CSSStyleRule: style property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The read\-only \f[B]\f[CB]style\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]CSSStyleRule\f[R] interface contains a
\f[CR]CSSStyleProperties\f[R] object representing the properties list in
this style rule\(cqs body.
.PP
Each CSS property supported by the browser is present on the object.
The properties that are not defined inline in the corresponding CSS
declaration are set to the empty string (\f[CR]\(dq\(dq\f[R]).
.SH VALUE
A \f[CR]CSSStyleProperties\f[R] object.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] Earlier versions of the specification returned a
\f[CR]CSSStyleDeclaration\f[R], which is now the base class of
\f[CR]CSSStyleProperties\f[R].
See the browser compatibility table for browser support information.
.RE
.PP
Although the \f[CR]style\f[R] property itself is read\-only in the sense
that you can\(cqt replace the \f[CR]CSSStyleProperties\f[R] object, you
can still assign to the \f[CR]style\f[R] property directly, which is
equivalent to assigning to its \f[CR]cssText\f[R] property.
You can also modify the \f[CR]CSSStyleProperties\f[R] object using the
\f[CR]setProperty()\f[R] and \f[CR]removeProperty()\f[R] methods.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Getting the styles for a style rule
The CSS below defines the style rule for the \f[CR]h1\f[R] selector,
which is represented in code by a \f[CR]CSSStyleRule\f[R] instance.
The declaration block is that part of the style rule that appears within
the braces and that actually provides the style definitions (for the
selector, the part that comes before the braces), which is represented
in code by the \f[CR]style\f[R] property.
.IP
.EX
h1 {
  \f[B]color\f[R]: pink;
}
.EE
.PP
Assuming the above style rule is the first rule in the document, it will
be the first \f[CR]CSSRule\f[R] returned by
\f[CR]document.styleSheets[0].cssRules\f[R].
\f[CR]myRules[0].style\f[R] returns a \f[CR]CSSStyleProperties\f[R]
object representing the declarations defined for \f[CR]h1\f[R].
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] myRules = document.styleSheets[0].cssRules;
console.log(myRules[0].style); \f[I]// a CSSStyleProperties representing the declarations on the h1.\f[R]
.EE
